		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You can use the Puppy live CD, or you can use the Ubuntu live CD. But then you would need a working CD drive. It might be time for a trip to <a href="http://www.apluscomputers.com/" class="postlink">a computer repair shop in your area</a>; they might be able to put in a working CD drive and reinstall Windows from the Certificate of Authenticity on the case.

		

